===Noun===

# A hypothetical, invented [[disease]] of the lungs, caused by inhaling mineral or metallic dust, such as [[silicon]] and [[quartzite]], over a long [[period]].  Usually used only as an example of the longest English word.

Often shortened to [[pneumonoconiosis]] or [[pneumoconiosis]].

===Etymology===

Late 19th Century, from Greek pneumo- 'lung' + ultra 'very' + microscopic + silico- 'silicon' + volcano + konis 'dust' + -osis 'disease'.













